#compdef bfc
# =============================================================================
# bfc — Wilfred Hughes's "industrial-grade brainfuck compiler" — a
#       Rust-implemented optimizing compiler for Urban Müller's
#       1993 esoteric language Brainfuck.  bfc demonstrates that a
#       Brainfuck compiler can be a SERIOUS optimizing compiler:
#       parses BF source to an internal `bfir` IR, applies a 9-pass
#       peephole optimizer (combine consecutive +/- operations,
#       move adjacent <>, eliminate dead loops, fold loop-zero
#       optimizations, multiply-add detection, scan-loop replacement,
#       cell-bounds analysis), then emits LLVM IR and links via
#       `llc` + `cc` to produce a standalone optimized executable.
#       Provides RUST-QUALITY ERROR DIAGNOSTICS for BF programs via
#       ariadne — when parsing or optimization fails, bfc emits
#       syntax-error reports with source-pointer highlights showing
#       the offending byte, surrounding lines for context, and
#       suggested fixes.  Used as a teaching example for compiler-
#       construction courses + as a working demonstration of Wilfred
#       Hughes's commitment to industrial-grade tooling even for
#       trivial languages.
#
# Author:  Wilfred Hughes (@Wilfred) — independent Rust developer
#          + author of `difftastic` (structural diff for
#          programming languages, 22000+ stars), `helpful`
#          (lightweight Rust UX library), `git-flame` (alternative
#          to git blame).  Wilfred is known for producing
#          industrial-quality Rust tools for niche problems with
#          extreme attention to UX details — bfc is a deliberate
#          showcase project demonstrating "what if a brainfuck
#          compiler had the same quality bar as GCC?"
# Source:  https://github.com/Wilfred/bfc
# CLI:     src/main.rs (uses clap-builder API + ariadne for
#                        diagnostic reporting on BF parse errors
#                        and optimization warnings)
# Library: zesterer/ariadne
#          ("[Ariadne has moved to Codeberg!] A fancy diagnostics &
#           error reporting crate" — Joshua "zesterer" Barretto's
